The Last Stand of Sir Shandler de Eberyon<br>
<br>
In the last few years <br>
when the snows never fell.<br>
There live a knight<br>
in the Winter's Dell<br>
<br>
A Knight as kind<br>
as the sun above.<br>
A Knight devoted<br>
to the Goddess of Love.<br>
<br>
A Knight that fought<br>
with calming words.<br>
A Knight that Jousted<br>
never on birds.<br>
<br>
Sir Shandler was <br>
a kindly, old man<br>
whose favorite foods <br>
were peaches and ham.<br>
<br>
Sir Shandler loved<br>
all that he saw.<br>
From the flowers in spring<br>
to the colors of Fall.<br>
<br>
He loved the beasts that dwell<br>
in their forrest abodes.<br>
He loved the people who wrapped<br>
their houses in bows.<br>
<br>
He was a knight as true<br>
as true as could be.<br>
A Knight as true,<br>
as Erollsi Marr would have be.<br>
<br>
Shandler was a patient <br>
and caring old man<br>
who'd give you the shirt of his back<br>
if it would help you to stand.<br>
<br>
He'd nail shingles to your roof<br>
to keep the rain off your head.<br>
He'd give his life dearly<br>
to make sure you'd not be dead.<br>
<br>
And if there's an emotion stronger than love<br>
who can take flight on wings of a dove<br>
I'd never have known it couldn't come from above<br>
for Sir Shander was all that dreamers belove.<br>
<br>
For from love comes <br>
fires deep from the heart<br>
that can burn and ravage <br>
all things apart.<br>
<br>
Fires that can sear, <br>
and fires that can rage.<br>
Fires that can melt, <br>
and fires that can encage.<br>
<br>
So when the darkness comes<br>
and seeps into your house.<br>
And you fear to tread<br>
lightly, like a mouse.<br>
<br>
Take courage, and drive <br>
that fear from your heart<br>
for Sir Shander de Eberyon <br>
shall protect your start.<br>
<br>
His love will drive off <br>
the darkness of pain,<br>
His love gives courage <br>
to try again.<br>
<br>
His love shines like <br>
the sun during the day,<br>
it dries eyes, heals wounds, <br>
any year of the day.<br>
<br>
And though Sir Shandler <br>
has fallen himself<br>
his love remains <br>
on everyone's shelf.<br>
<br>
And though Sir Shandler <br>
has made his last stand,<br>
His love remains, <br>
and that is most grand.<br>
<br>
For love is the strongest of emotions there is,<br>
and Erollsi Marr gave Sir Shandler his.<br>
